The bill includes provisions that will make it harder for kids to receive the nutrition they need. 

This bill could cause over 18 million American children to lose access to free school meals. For many of these kids, the free lunch they get at school is the only nutritious meal they get that day.

Kids will go hungry and their academic performance and attendance will suffer.

The bill cuts $300 billion in SNAP, which over 40 million Americans depend on. 

This will cost farmers $30 billion in lost farm income at a time when they are already being squeezed by high input costs and low prices.

Medicaid is a program that serves low-income families across Minnesota - families that cannot afford a $35 copay every time they need to see a doctor.

Republicans are sneaking in this extra cost that will do nothing but punish sick Americans and deter them from accessing the health care they need.

Republicans’ plans to cut Medicaid will be fatal for rural America.

More than half of all children and 18% of adults in rural areas are covered by Medicaid. Cutting Medicaid would worsen health outcomes, especially for folks with chronic illnesses, like diabetes, heart disease, and cancer, which are leading causes of death for rural Americans.

Nearly 14 million people (and likely more) by 2034 would lose health coverage and become uninsured. 

That includes 8.6 million Americans who rely on Medicaid and the ACA Marketplace to access the affordable, life-saving health care they need.
